# 10. Validation Checklist

Before committing:

- [ ] all imports follow correct ordering
- [ ] no relative cross-package imports exist
- [ ] no feature-to-feature direct imports
- [ ] no domain → data/presentation violations
- [ ] only public APIs used across packages
- [ ] generated files not directly imported
- [ ] preflight passes

---

# 10. Enforcement Severity

- **MUST NOT** = build-breaking architectural violation
- **SHOULD NOT** = refactor required soon
- **PREFERRED** = improves maintainability but not blocking

---

# 11. Output Expectation for Agents

When fixing import issues, agents must:

## Report

- violated boundaries
- corrected import paths
- affected modules

## Confirm

- dependency graph still valid
- no feature coupling introduced